description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are recruiting for Housekeepers to join our bank team. You will be working on a flexible basis, as and when required to help deliver vital services to patients and members of the public.&lt;/span&gt; As a member of the bank team you will be able to choose from a variety of shifts that work around you to create better work life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the housekeeping team you will be serving breakfast to patients, and undertaking general and specialized cleaning, ensuring the ward/department is cleaned to a high standard. You will be required to frequently use heavy machinery such as buffing machines, as well as vacuums and carpet shampooer’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for candidates with good availability during the during the day, Monday - Friday, also available to work some weekends. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our bank team provide essential support to frontline staff, in return you will receive full training, competitive rates of pay with enhancements for unsociable hours and a large range of discounts and benefits available to NHS staff. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All candidates will be expected to sit a written assessment of English and Maths at the interview if they are invited to attend. Those who do not meet the minimum standard will not progress to the interview stage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role will not attract a visa please ensure you have the right to work in the UK before applying&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
